<taxonomicName authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1850" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Senaspis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Senaspis" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Senaspis</taxonomicName>
Macquart, 1850: 437. Type species: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1850" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Senaspis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Senaspis flaviceps" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="flaviceps">Senaspis flaviceps</taxonomicName>
Macquart, 1850 (by monotypy).
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
<taxonomicName authority="Bezzi, 1912" authorityName="Bezzi" authorityYear="1912" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Protylocera" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Protylocera" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Protylocera</taxonomicName>
Bezzi, 1912: 414 [unnecessary replacement name].
</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
<taxonomicName authority="Hull, 1949" authorityName="Hull" authorityYear="1949" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Triatylosus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Triatylosus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Triatylosus</taxonomicName>
Hull, 1949: 398 (as subgenus). Type species: 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Xylota" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Xylota dibaphus" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="dibaphus">Xylota dibaphus</taxonomicName>
Walker, 1849 (by original designation).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="83" type="generic diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Generic diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="83">
<taxonomicName authorityName="Macquart" authorityYear="1850" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Senaspis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Senaspis" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Senaspis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species are morphologically characterized by the combination of the following characters: eyes bare and maculate (less conspicuous in dried specimens), dorsal facets in male usually only slightly larger than ventral facets, more pronounced so in 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. dibapha" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="dibapha">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">S. dibapha</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Walker, 1849) and 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. nigrita" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="nigrita">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">S. nigrita</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(Bigot, 1859); antennal arista bare; frons in lateral view with distinct protuberance; wing with cell r1 usually closed and petiolate, or narrowly open at most (see Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 68–73" captionStartId="F21" captionText="Figures 68 - 73. Senaspis species, right wing 68 S. elliotii Austen (♂) 69 - 71 S. elliotii Austen close-up apical end 72 S. flaviceps Macquart (♂) 73 S. haemorrhoa (Gerstaecker) (♂)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1003.56557.figures68-73" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/486717" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">69</figureCitation>
) (if distinctly open then hyaline, without dark markings; see 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Herve-Bazin" baseAuthorityYear="1914" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Senaspis" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Senaspis pennata" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pennata">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">Senaspis pennata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 77–79" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figures 77 - 79. Senaspis species, right wing 77 S. umbrifera (Walker) (♂ holotype) 78 S. xanthorrhoea (Bezzi) (♂) 79 S. pennata (Herve-Bazin) (♀)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.1003.56557.figures77-79" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/486719" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">79</figureCitation>
); vein R4+5 strongly sinuate; thorax with triangular (dorsomedial) part of anepimeron bare, katepimeron bare or pilose at least in dorsal part; metatibia with conspicuous pile on at least apical half ventrally (except in 
<taxonomicName genus="S." lsidName="S. flaviceps" pageId="0" pageNumber="83" rank="species" species="flaviceps">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="83">S. flaviceps</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
